'''Robin Harvey''' was a sportsman from [[St Columb Major]] in [[Cornwall]],was educated at [[Blundell's School]] and formally represented his County in both Cricket (1959 - 1971) and Rugby.<ref>[http://www.thisiscornwall.co.uk/homepagenews/Memory-Lane/article-486913-detail/article.html Memory Lane] </ref>

==County Cricket==
He was Captain of [[Cornwall County Cricket Club]] and emmigrated to South Africa in 1968. In 1969 he became the first Cornishman to be awarded the [[Wilfred Rhodes]] Trophy for having topped the batting average in the competition that season.<ref>http://archive.falmouthpacket.co.uk/2004/12/16/8403.html</ref>

==County Rugby==
Harvey played for Cornwall County team on eight occasions. His father Geoffrey Harvey was also an accomplished rugby player and was captain of The Hornets RFC. <ref>[http://clubs.rfu.com/Clubs/portals/NewquayHornetsRFC/ClubHistory8996.aspx History of Newquay Hornets]</ref>

